</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="77D8652CFFE5FF9DFD02FE1BBA62FDE7" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="3F7D36A7FFE5FF9DFD02FE1BBA62FDE7" blockId="10.[701,1228,211,532]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">ETYMOLOGY: The specific epithet is from the Greek and means ‘‘in the Earth,’’ or ‘‘pertaining to the nether world,’’ and is a reference to the fact that the species is known only as a compression fossil.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
